-- Mexico Stocks: Alfa, Geo, Grupo Mexico, Industrias Penoles Gain
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-03T18:25:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/mexico-stocks-alfa-geo-grupo-mexico-industrias-penoles-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:01 p.m. local time.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  rose 0.5 percent to 37,503.34.  Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities higher after data
showed manufacturing in the U.S., Mexico’s largest trading
partner, grew in December at the fastest pace in six months.  Corp. Geo SAB (GEOB)  , Mexico’s second-largest
homebuilder, rose 2.7 percent to 18.06 pesos.  Urbi Desarrollos
Urbanos SAB (URBI*)  , Mexico’s third-largest homebuilder,
gained 2.8 percent to 16.58 pesos.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA)  , the
world’s largest producer of aluminum engine heads, advanced 2.3
percent to 158 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, gained 1.9 percent to 37.53 pesos. Copper
futures for March delivery rose as much as 3 percent in  New
York .  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 1 percent to 618 pesos. Silver futures
for March delivery rose as much as 6.5 percent to $29.73 an
ounce on the Comex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
